text: Jadwiga Barańska (21 October 1935 – 24 October 2024) was a Polish actress and screenwriter. She was born in Łódź, Poland. Her career began in 1958 and she retired in 2002. She was known for her role as Anna Constantia von Brockdorff in 1968 movie Countess Cosel. Barańska died on 24 October 2024 in Los Angeles, California, three days after her 89th birthday. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1935 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Actors from Łódź Category:Writers from Łódź Category:Polish screenwriters Category:Polish movie actors Category:Polish television actors Category:Polish stage actors
